                            <comment id="71740" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 18 Nov 2013 01:01:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LU-1817&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71738" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 18 Nov 2013 00:59:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test nodes are:&lt;br/&gt;
MDS: client-26vm3&lt;br/&gt;
OSS: client-26vm4&lt;br/&gt;
Client1: client-26vm6&lt;br/&gt;
Client2: client-26vm5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test scripts were running on the Client1 (client-26vm6). When the client1 try to stop the system, it failed to stop the client2 (client-26vm5) as following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;pdsh@client-26vm6: gethostbyname(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;client-26vm5&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) failed
 sanity-scrub test_4: @@@@@@ FAIL: Fail to stop client! 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the test has nothing related with the client2. I do not think it is Lustre issue, instead, it looks more like DNS related issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
